public class Solution extends GuessGame {
    public int guessNumber(int n) {
        int left = 1, right = n;
        while (left <= right) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            int result = guess(mid);
            if (result == 0) return mid;
            else if (result == -1) right = mid - 1;
            else left = mid + 1;
        }
        return -1; // This line will never be reached given the constraints.
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a binary search algorithm to efficiently guess the number. It maintains a search range [left, right] and iteratively narrows it down until the correct number is found. The key strength is its logarithmic time complexity, making it suitable for large inputs. 
